docs.lead_paragraph: Nalini Jones reviews Jason Reynolds’s latest book, “Look Both Ways,” in this week’s issue. In 2015, Kekla Magoon wrote for the Book Review about “All American Boys,” a Y.A. novel that Reynolds wrote with Brendan Kiely about a black teenager and a white teenager grappling with an instance of police brutality.

headline.main: Revisiting Jason Reynolds and Brendan Kiely’s ‘All American Boys’

docs.abstract: A California school district said it was investigating and apologized if students felt “discomfort” about what happened.

docs.lead_paragraph: A school district near Sacramento, Calif., said it is investigating an episode in which a teacher threw away student posters related to the Black Lives Matter movement.

headline.main: Teacher Threw Away Students’ Black Lives Matter Posters, A.C.L.U. Says
